# NSIndexSetIterator

**Structure**

An iterator suitable for enumerating the elements of an index set.

## Declaration

```swift
struct NSIndexSetIterator
```

## Overview

You typically obtain an index set iterator by calling the [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSIndexSet/makeIterator()] function of an [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSIndexSet] instance.

## Iteration

- **NSEnumerator**: An abstract class whose subclasses enumerate collections of objects, such as arrays and dictionaries.
- **NSFastEnumeration**: A protocol that objects adopt to support fast enumeration.
- **NSFastEnumerationIterator**
- **NSEnumerationOptions**: Options for block enumeration operations.
- **NSSortOptions**: Options for block sorting operations.
